message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "afi: A Python Library for Freedom-Based Structural Analysis of Swarm Intelligence"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-03-04"
url: "https://github.com/iamgoncalo/afi-python-library"
repository-code: "https://github.com/iamgoncalo/afi-python-library"
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Melo
    given-names: Gonçalo
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0008-6255-7724"
    email: hi@planta.design
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher, Porto, Portugal"
keywords:
  - swarm intelligence
  - exploration-exploitation
  - complex adaptive systems
  - structural analysis
  - navigability
  - freedom
  - perception
  - distortion
abstract: >-
  afi computes Freedom F = P/D — the ratio of Perception
  (differentiation capacity) to Distortion (structural resistance)
  — across adaptive systems. It provides the first algorithm-agnostic
  exploration-exploitation transition metric E(t) = σ[F]/μ[F],
  convergence bounds, gradient dynamics, and anomaly decomposition
  for swarm intelligence research.
references:
  - type: article
    authors:
